 <H1>Example Decomposition</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Decompositions should be used only when needed.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>SNLRWH has FDs  S        SNLRWH  and  R       W
<LI>Second FD causes violation of 3NF; W values repeatedly associated with R values.  Easiest way to fix this is to create a relation RW to store these associations, and to remove W from the main schema: 
<LI>i.e., we decompose SNLRWH into SNLRH and RW 
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>The information to be stored consists of SNLRWH tuples.  If we just store the projections of these tuples onto SNLRH and RW, are there any potential problems that we should be aware of?</H2>
</UL></P>
